TRAC MPIAE Changes
===================


Current WIP
-----------
* FIX: fix missing i18n of the modal that shows up when clicking the Submit Day button


Version 0.12.0 -- Study creation via API possible, UX improvements
--------------------------------------------------------------------
* NEW: improve frontend UX and design (uncovered timelines, clearer active timeline, ...)
* NEW: support creating new study via API (required moving available activities into DB)
* NEW: allow changing study start/end time via admin page
* NEW: development: add Docker dev environment
* NEW: development: increase test coverage, test on chrome, webkit and firefox


Version 0.11.0 -- Improved delete UX and other improvements
------------------------------------------------------------
* NEW: add support for return_url URL param, see #53
* NEW: keep unsaved activities when reloading page (e.g., F5)
* NEW: add context menu (right-click) on desktop with delete activity button
* NEW: add delete activity reminder in template message. FIX: make message text match exact button name
* NEW: add supported_languages entry to studies_config.json for each study, make backend use it
* NEW: add more project metadata to pyproject.toml


Version 0.10.0 -- Template data from other users, switch to submitted days
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
* NEW: allow deleting activities via long-press on desktop, show red animation before delete on desktop and mobile
* NEW: allow copying activities from another user as template via template_user=X url argument, and add tests for it. see #51
* FIX show i18n weekday correctly in first supported language
* NEW: implement buttons to edit previously submitted days, implements #44
* FIX: prevent user from deleting activities in inactive timelines, fixes #50
* NEW: allow selecting timelines with keyboard/TAB
* CHG: rename setting STUDY_NAME to DEFAULT_STUDY_NAME
* NEW: allow downloading studies_config per study in admin interface
* NEW: allow re-creating ratings from downloaded studies_config file in db at backend startup
* NEW: add retry on backend errors, and proper error reporting on final fail
* FIX: show correct backend status message in footer in frontend when connected


Version 0.9.7 -- DE language support, bug fixes, dev improvements
-------------------------------------------------------------------
* NEW: Add German translation
* CHG: Allow extra languages for custom texts in studies_config, but warn if translated activitites files are missing and do not consider that language as available, i.e., do not send to frontend for selection dropdown
* FIX: rename language code 'fn' to 'fi', proper ISO 639-1 language code for Finnish
* FIX: failed backend request on submitting data for a day could leave UI in broken state because it did not properly check for and react to backend submission response
* NEW: development only: use guvicorn and watchdog as dev servers to better support many concurrent e2e test workers. Also allows to catch bugs during parallel worker startup in dev, e.g., startup functions that are not thread-safe.


Version 0.9.6 -- Implement full i18n
-------------------------------------
* NEW: support several different language versions of activities files, and requesting / sending them to frontend
* NEW: Remove hard-coded english lang strings in frontend and move to locales/ files
* NEW: admin interface multi-lang improvements, e.g., allow preview of activities in all available languages
* BRK: change studies_config format to support multi-lang studies with per-language custom text for intro and thanks-you pages
* FIX: replace all cloud/CDN access with local copies in src/assets/ dir, implements #46


Version 0.9.5 -- Admin interface overhaul II
----------------------------------------------
* NEW: Dramatically improve information in admin interface
* NEW: improve usage reminder banner text to include 'd' key for delete info, as users may have trouble with DEL
* FIX: make all times in DB TZ-aware
* NEW: development only: add test scripts, make e2e test more robust to slower loading on CI


Version 0.9.4 -- More frontend corner case fixes, UX improvements and tests
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
* NEW: keep timeline height identical, no matter whether active or not, to prevent visual jumping on selecting the other one
* NEW: make it clearer which timelines is active/editable by adding frame
* FIX: fix bug that if you delete activities from timeline in mobile view, then switch, they still exist in desktop view
* CHG: make instructions banner and template banner stay until closed. make instructions banner show up only on first day.
* FIX: under certain conditions activities can move timelines due to bug with active timeline handling
* NEW: add more E2E tests, including for activity deletion test, resizing activities on timeline, and all fixed bugs


Version 0.9.3 -- Fix more frontend issues, prevent regression with E2E tests
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
* NEW: development only: fix E2E test CI workflow and make tests work. Add various E2E tests.
* NEW: add test that ensures template activities for both timelines are kept on submitting a day
* FIX: fix issue #42 'Shrinking browser window to below desktop size removes activity display' by persisting unsaved activity items to local storage on view switch desktop/mobile, and re-using them if appropriate
* NEW: make timelines stay in place, no matter whether active or not. implements #45.


Version 0.9.2 -- Admin interface overhaul
------------------------------------------
* FIX: Disable activities download button for study if it has no activities recorded yet
* FIX: fix download paths in admin interface when served with rootpath
* CHG: Use our custom instructions page by default. Will need to implement by-study instructions page later.
* CHG: better status report in /health endpoint of API, changed returned response values and made it clear what they mean
* FIX: development only: copy config files in dev_both... script.
* WIP: development only: the E2E tests are still WIP and broken (unchanged from release 0.9.1)


Version 0.9.1 -- More bug fixes, skip button
---------------------------------------------
* CHG: refactor activity loading to happen in one central place.
* FIX: Replace hard-coded use of local activities_config.json file everywhere with new central activity loading.
* FIX: when selecting an activitiy, ensure all others are unselected.
* FIX: when changing page, ensure currently selected activity (if any) is cleared
* NEW: add skip button in frontend
* WIP: development only: adding E2E tests with playwright. Currently still failing due to wrong expectations on start URL. Ignore for now.


Version 0.9.0 -- Small fixes
-----------------------------
* NEW: on startup, report for each study the JSON activities file URL and the number of activities in DB for this study.
* FIX: remove swedish words in brackets from English activities version
* NEW: in frontend, add new page footer with new backend status indicator message
* NEW: development: add integration tests running on CI server
* CHG: update activities and studies files


Version 0.8.0 -- Unify FE + BE repos, make integration tests work on CI
------------------------------------------------------------------------
* NEW: Move the frontend code into this repo under new frontend/ sub dir
* CHG: Move the backend code into new backend/ sub dir
* NEW: Add GitHub CI workflow for integration tests and a first test


Version 0.6.3 -- Various bug fixes, start i18n support
------------------------------------------------------
* NEW: support timeline min_coverage property, fixed #41
* CHG: update text experiment activities again
* NEW: finish dev scripts for nginx local, now supporting very easy testing with FastAPI rootpath set
* NEW: add default_language property to studies (cfg file, db, api)
* FIX: Fix bugs #39/#40 (in frontend, deleted activity still blocked space on timeline)


Version 0.6.2 -- Fix Editing template activities
-----------------------------------------------
* FIX: do not use ID of source activity when sending template activity, compute startTime and endTime for backend activities properly in frontend. Fixes bug in frontend that one cannot change times of activities.
* compute ISO format start_time and end_time in ISO time format like 08:30:00 from the minutes after midnight in backend and send with activites. a service for the frontend.
* add lots of dev scripts to repo that make it easier to test under conditions closer to production (nginx with reverse proxy setup, fastapi rootpath)


Version 0.6.1 -- Support display_name for days
------------------------------------------------
* NEW: support display_name property for days in cfg file, database and API


Version 0.6.0 -- Save and send activity category field
-------------------------------------------------------
* NEW: Save category field for activities when frontend sends data
* BRK: New category field for activity in database will require db migration or re-creation



Version 0.5.1 -- Startup bug fix
